results.name: Number of distinct prime signatures that occur among the divisors of the n-th prime signature number (A025487(n)).
comment: Also the number of members of A025487 that divide A025487(n).
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 5 members of A025487 divide A025487(6) = 12 (namely, 1, 2, 4, 6 and 12); therefore, a(6) = 5.
xref: Rearrangement of A115728, A115729 and A238690.
A116473(n) is the number of times n appears in the sequence.
